      "solution": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Ans. A. 0.83</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Explanation:</u></strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>RDA Safe Protein Requirement&nbsp;</strong>of <strong>High Quality Protein</strong>:</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">1-5 years age: 0.94 g/kg/d</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;6-10 years old children: 0.91 g/kg/d</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;Adolescent boys: 0.88 g/kg/d</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;Adolescents girls: 0.86 g/kg/d</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">&nbsp;Adult man/woman (Sedentary/Moderate): 0.83 g/kg/d</span></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Educational Objective:</u></strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>RDA Safe Protein&nbsp;</strong>Requirement of <strong>High Quality Protein</strong> for <strong>Adult man/woman</strong> (Sedentary/Moderate) is <strong>0.83 g/kg/d</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Ref</u>: Park 26<sup>th</sup> edition (page 724)</strong></span></p>",
