      "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\">A 58-year-old diabetic patient is working on improving her diet to better manage her blood sugar levels. She is particularly interested in understanding the glycemic index of different foods and how they can impact her glucose control. Which of the following food options has a low glycemic index?</span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q2582159",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 34479,
      "difficulty_level": "intermediate",
      "subjects_id": [
        7
      ],
      "solution": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Ans. D. Lentils</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Option D:</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Glycemic Index&nbsp;</strong>of <strong>Lentil</strong> is <strong>21-33</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:black;font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Glycemic response&nbsp;</strong>(GR) of a <strong>food</strong> is a <strong>measure</strong> of that <strong>food’s ability</strong> to <strong>raise blood sugar</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:black;font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Glycemic index&nbsp;</strong>implies <strong>value assigned</strong> to <strong>each food item</strong> on how much after <strong>consumption</strong>, can <strong>increase</strong> the <strong>blood sugar levels</strong>.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:black;font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Glycemic index scale is 0 to 100 when using glucose as the standard.</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Explanation:&nbsp;</u></strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">Glycemic Index of&nbsp;</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Option&nbsp;A</strong>. Potato - <strong>65</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Option B</strong>. Watermelon - <strong>73</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Option C</strong>. Corn flakes - <strong>83</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Educational Objective:</u></strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>GLYCEMIC INDEX OF FOOD ITEMS</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Low GI</strong> (GI ≤ 55): Most <strong>fruits and vegetables</strong> (EXCEPT potato/watermelon/sweet potato), Whole grains, Beans,&nbsp;Pasta, Lentils</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Medium GI</strong> (GI 56 – 69): <strong>Sucrose</strong>, <strong>Basmati rice</strong>, <strong>Brown rice</strong></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>High GI</strong> (GI ≥ 70): <strong>Corn flakes</strong>, <strong>Baked potato</strong>, <strong>White bread</strong>, Candy bar, Syrupy food, Jasmine rice.</span></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Ref</u>: Park 26<sup>th</sup> edition (page 704)</strong></span></p>",
