      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">A 25-year-old male presents to the outpatient department with concerns about night blindness and xerosis cutis. As part of his evaluation, the physician considers potential nutritional deficiencies that could contribute to his symptoms. Based on these clinical features, a deficiency in which vitamin is suspected, and what is the Recommended Dietary Allowance (RDA) for this vitamin for an adult male of his age?</span></p>",
