        7
      ],
      "solution": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Ans.&nbsp;A.1000</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Explanation:</u></strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Daily requirement&nbsp;</strong>of <strong>Vitamin A</strong> in <strong>adult males</strong> and <strong>females</strong> in <strong>1000 microgram/day</strong>.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>RDA of Vitamin A&nbsp;</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">Adult Male: 1000 mcg/day</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">Adult Female: 840 mcg/day</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">Pregnancy: 900 mcg/day</span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">Lactation: 950 mcg/day</span></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>RDA of some important nutrients&nbsp;</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2024/08/12/screenshot-2024-08-12-102206.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"280\"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Educational Objective:</u></strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">The <strong>RDA for vitamin A</strong> for an <strong>adult male</strong> is <strong>1000 µg</strong> of <strong>retinol equivalents</strong> per day.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Ref</u>: Park 26<sup>th</sup> edition (page 726)</strong></span></p>",
